cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a self-supervised learning framework for visual odometry that incorporates correlation of consecutive frames and takes advantage of adversarial learning. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as visual odometry is an important task in robotics for navigation and localization. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a deep learning framework for self-supervised visual odometry. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a framework that learns a compact representation of frame-to-frame correlation and takes advantage of Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN). 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper proposes a deep learning framework that incorporates sequential information and adversarial learning.
